      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tech 2010</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eric Rosenbloom letter on Andrew Sullivan's June 11 article in special issue on millennium's social issues holds access to Web is only free to those who can afford it</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Andrew Sullivan says that ''the Web is still largely free to anyone with a modem and phone line.'' One also needs, however, a computer connected to that modem (with all the software and support and maintenance and peripherals) and usually a good credit card to secure Internet service. I am reminded of a line from the movie ''Withnail &amp; I'': ''Free to those who can afford it.''</p>
        <p>Eric Rosenbloom</p>
        <p>New York</p>
      </block>
